SIMPLE: wedge-tailed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wedge-tailed
<hw>Wedge"-tailed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a tail which has the middle pair of feathers longest, the
rest successively and decidedly shorter, and all more or less attenuate;
-- said of certain birds. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <cref>Wood
hoopoe</cref>, under <er>Wood</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wedge-tailed eagle</b></col>, <cd>an Australian eagle
(<spn>Aquila audax</spn>) which feeds on various small species of
kangaroos, and on lambs; -- called also <altname>mountain
eagle</altname>, <altname>bold eagle</altname>, and <altname>eagle
hawk</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Wedge-tailed gull</b></col>, <cd>an
arctic gull (<spn>Rhodostethia rosea</spn>) in which the plumage is
tinged with rose; -- called also <altname>Ross's
gull</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wedgewise</ent>⟦br⟧
